Description:
VICTORIAN TERRACE WITH A TOUCH OF CLASS
Superbly updated with an architecturally designed renovation, this classic Victorian terrace takes advantage of natural light and boasts magnificent period features just a short walk from Collingwood's funky shops, cafes, parks and schools. With glorious high ceilings, polished floorboards and 100 per cent wool carpets in its three generous bedrooms, it offers a spacious feel throughout, with a beautifully finished first-floor master bedroom that has double-glazed windows and an ensuite. The stylish lounge boasts three exquisite stained-glass windows and opens into a light-filled kitchen with Technika oven, stone benches and access through large glass sliding doors to the established Japanese-style garden, which includes a soothing water feature. Other highlights are off-street parking from Little Abbot St, wall heater, ample storage and picture rails throughout.
Insights: 153 Keele Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2015 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Split Level - Light filled - Warehouse Delight
If you are seeking a generously sized warehouse apartment that blends together fabulous outdoor living with superb indoor entertaining, then look no further than 23/78 Oxford St Collingwood. Situated on Oxford St and with original warehouse features, this large apartment is laid out over two levels with a wonderful floorplan offering loads of downstairs living and separate 2 bedroom accommodation on the upper level. Comprises open plan living, modern European appliance kitchen area, light filled deck with favourable northern aspect, downstairs powder room, plus two great sized upstairs bedrooms with BIR, central bathroom, and 2nd outdoor area and deck. Enhanced by security entry, storage cage and off street parking. Moments from Smith, Gertrude, Brunswick St, East Melbourne, Richmond, CBD and more.

Description:
One Street back from Smith St in the heart of Collingwood....with 2 car spaces!
Investors and owner occupiers take note of this spectacular 2 bedroom apartment in the heart of Smith & Brunswick streets' vibrant cafe / restaurant culture.
One of the largest and most generous floor plans in the boutique block of 12, this apartment is situated at the front of the block over looking the historic Foy & Gibson buildings. The apartment features a full width east facing entertainers balcony, secure OSP for 2, lift access, split system air-conditioning, ceiling fans, panel heating, BIR, hardwood polished floors and loads of natural light. Added to this is a contemporary kitchen with gas cooktop, dishwasher and stone bench tops, and a modern central bathroom - separate full sized European laundry.
This property is conveniently located only a walking distance from Smith Street shopping precinct, Proud Mary's Cafe, and the newly opened Coles. It is close to public transport and only a bike ride away from Melbourne CBD. These factors considered this property is ideal for either an owner occupier or savvy investor.
INVESTMENT / OWNER OCCUPIER
** The property is currently leased until 15th July 2016 @ $550 p/w
** Depreciation allowances 15/16 FY - $7,413.00
** Strong Rental demand
** Extended settlement terms considered
Michael Furlong : 0425 713 571

Description:
CAPTIVATING WAREHOUSE CONVERSION, TRANQUIL AND SPACIOUS
Situated beyond the original Craig & Hales factory walls, this cleverly transformed residence boasts authentic warehouse character with soaring ceilings, exposed trusses and cutting edge style to provide a private & secure inner city haven ideally situated in this increasingly popular location close to Smith St & Brunswick St shops/cafes & transport options. The very functional floor plan showcases 3 bedrooms (including an impressive 1st floor master bedroom with ensuite & massive walk in robe), stylish 2nd bathroom & concealed laundry, designer open plan kitchen with stainless steel finishes, striking living & dining zones flowing to a landscaped high-walled courtyard oasis with excellent car access via roller door and ROW. Featuring custom storage, polished concrete floors, air conditioning and quality appointments, this impressive warehouse residence is well worth your inspection. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
FOY & GIBSON WAREHOUSE SPLENDOUR
Brilliantly updated to create an exceptionally stylish and secure inner urban domain over three impressively spacious levels, sitting just behind the historic warehouse facade!
- 2 large bedrooms luxuriously spacious master suite with huge walk in robe / dressing room
- Unique and sun lit living and dining space ethanol fireplace on custom Caesar Stone top cabinetry, polished floor boards
- Sleek designer kitchen Blanco cooktop & pyrolytic oven, Caesar Stone bench tops, Integrated fridge & dishwasher

This generously proportioned property has all the hallmarks for exceptional modern living. The large levels create flexibility in the floor plan (why not add another bedroom on the top floor!). This property is also enhanced by its premier inner city local just moments from brilliant restaurants and cafes, the CBD, transport and so much more!

Quality at every turn, the home's vogue interior boasts three bedrooms (large master with WIR and ensuite) and stylish main central bathroom. Flexible living spaces include large ground-floor 3rd bedroom/lounge or home office, upstairs possible 4th bedroom/sitting area, plus spacious top-floor open-plan living/dining area and study nook, stone-top kitchen with stainless steel Blanco appliances and sliding door to balcony, ideal for entertaining and enjoying the views. Add to this ducted heating and cooling, security system, quality carpets and solid timber floors, ample storage cupboards, laundry and private double garage (remote-controlled) with internal entry. On the fringe of East Melbourne, Fitzroy and Richmond, it is within walking distance to the MCG, trams, Victoria Street restaurants, North Richmond Station, Fitzroy Gardens and the CBD. Brilliant!
